    "answer": "To implement cross-factory dependencies natively:\n\n1. REST API polling: Use a Web activity in Factory A that targets the ADF REST API endpoint of Factory B: `https://management.azure.com/subscriptions/{subId}/resourceGroups/{rg}/providers/Microsoft.DataFactory/factories/{factoryB}/pipelineruns/{runId}?api-version=2018-06-01`.\n\n2. Until Loop Wrapper: Place the Web activity inside an Until activity. Configure the loop expression to evaluate the status returned by the Web activity. Loop until the status equals 'Succeeded' or fails ('Failed', 'Cancelled').\n\n3. Wait Timer: Insert a Wait activity inside the loop (e.g., 2 minutes) to prevent rate-limiting/throttling on the Azure Resource Manager API, creating a native polling mechanism that blocks Factory A until Factory B finishes.",
