    "question": "Why does a variable mutated inside a ForEach activity exhibit erratic, non-deterministic values when isSequential is set to false, and what architectural pattern prevents this?",
    "answer": "1. Root Cause: Variables in ADF are scoped at the pipeline level, not the ForEach loop block level. When `isSequential` is set to false, multiple parallel threads execute concurrently and read/write to the same global variable, causing race conditions and non-deterministic state corruption.\n\n2. Prevention Pattern: To store thread-local states, avoid mutating pipeline variables. Instead, pass the current loop item (`@item()`) directly into a child pipeline using the Execute Pipeline activity. Variables declared inside the child pipeline are scoped uniquely to each child execution thread, ensuring isolation and preventing race conditions during parallel processing.",
