    "answer": "1. Azure Batch: Spawns a full VM compute instance (or uses an existing pool). Ideal for heavy, long-running, and complex file conversions (e.g., running Custom Python scripts, executing EXEs). It has higher cold start/scheduling overhead, making it unsuitable for real-time low-latency operations.\n\n2. Azure Function: Serverless, lightweight, and triggers instantly. Ideal for small, low-latency transformations (e.g., hashing a single string, executing light business rules). It has a strict execution limit (default 5 minutes, max 10) and is billed per execution, providing high efficiency for row-by-row API helper tasks.",
