    "answer": "1. Slices generation: When the start date of a Tumbling Window Trigger is set to a past date (backfilling), the trigger immediately generates all historical hourly or daily slices between the start date and the current date.\n\n2. Concurrency limit: Slices execute concurrently up to the trigger's concurrency setting (e.g., 50 parallel runs). Modification via ARM deployment resets the trigger state, causing it to regenerate and rerun all slices, so ensure concurrency limits are configured to prevent target database resource saturation during deployments.",
