    "answer": "1. Activity Properties: Inside the pipeline execution metadata, every completed activity contains runtime timestamps. Access these using: `@activity('CopyTask').output.executionDetails[0].duration` (for copy activities).\n\n2. Dynamic Calculation: For general activities, use the `ticks` function to calculate the difference between start and end times:\n`@div(sub(ticks(activity('TaskName').output.endTime), ticks(activity('TaskName').output.startTime)), 10000000)` to get duration in seconds, and log this to your custom DB using a Web or Stored Proc activity.",
