    "answer": "1. The Bottleneck: Millions of small files create extreme metadata overhead (file open/close operations) in both Blob Storage and the SHIR file enumeration engine, degrading PolyBase throughput.\n\n2. Optimization strategy: Instead of loading files individually, merge the JSON files during ingestion. Use a Copy Activity that merges small files into larger consolidated files (e.g., 100MB Parquet or CSV files) in ADLS Gen2 before triggering PolyBase. This reduces file metadata checks and allows PolyBase to read data in parallel using optimal block sizes, increasing load speed.",
