    "question": "What is the impact of utilizing object storage intelligent tiering systems on the deterministic predictability of query performance SLAs for real-time executive dashboards connected to a data lake query engine?",
    "answer": "1. Performance SLA Risk: Intelligent-Tiering automatically moves files to cold access tiers if they are not read. When an executive opens a dashboard that queries these files, the query engine experiences hydration latency delays.\n\n2. Mitigation: Configure the query coordinator to run daily preload queries for active dashboard ranges, or pin crucial tables to the S3 Frequent Access tier to ensure deterministic latency SLAs.",
