    "answer": "1. Vendor Portability: Storing data in open formats (Iceberg/Delta) allows swapping query engines (e.g., Databricks to Snowflake or Trino) in days without rewriting physical files.\n\n2. Cost Flexibility: Bypasses proprietary database storage fees, allowing you to select the cheapest cloud compute nodes and query engines dynamically, optimizing infrastructure spend.",
