    "answer": "When Change Data Feed (CDF) is enabled on a table, the Delta engine writes change data files (e.g., inserts, pre-image, post-image deletes) to the `_change_data/` folder. Running `OPTIMIZE` applies V-Order optimization. 1) OPTIMIZE rewrites active data Parquet files into V-Ordered files. 2) OPTIMIZE does not modify or duplicate the historical change log records in the `ChangeData` directory. 3) The historical CDF logs remain unchanged to preserve the change history. However, any subsequent write operations that generate change data will write those change records as V-Ordered Parquet files, ensuring format consistency for future reads.",
