    "question": "Explain the architectural division of labor between the SQL Analytics Endpoint control plane and the distributed Polaris query engine when executing a multi-million row cross-database join.",
    "answer": "When executing a cross-database join via the SQL Endpoint: 1) The Control Plane authenticates the user, parses the T-SQL query, checks catalog permissions, and generates a logical query plan. 2) The Logical Plan is passed to the Polaris engine. 3) Polaris compiles the logical plan into a distributed physical execution plan consisting of parallelized tasks. 4) Polaris coordinates worker nodes to read the Delta Parquet files directly from OneLake. 5) Compute nodes execute the physical joins, aggregations, and shuffles in parallel. The Control Plane only handles orchestration, security handshake, and returning the final result set, while Polaris handles the compute-intensive distributed execution.",
