    "answer": "1) `CTAS` is a metadata-driven operation that creates a new Delta table. The engine writes new Parquet files in parallel across compute nodes and registers the schema. It has minimal transactional overhead, making it fast. 2) `INSERT INTO ... SELECT` appends to an existing table. The engine must validate schema compatibility, check constraints, write new files, and append to the active Delta log. This requires more transaction log coordination to prevent conflicts with concurrent readers/writers, making it slower than CTAS on large datasets.",
