    "answer": "When the SQL Endpoint detects non-deterministic functions in a subquery: 1) The optimizer cannot push down the predicates to the Parquet reader level. 2) The engine must scan the table and evaluate the non-deterministic function in memory for every row. 3) This degrades performance, as file skipping is disabled. To optimize, materialize the non-deterministic value in a variable before running the query: `DECLARE @Date DATETIME = GETDATE(); SELECT * FROM tbl WHERE Col = @Date;` which allows the optimizer to treat the value as a constant and push down the filter.",
