    "question": "How do you configure and query Azure Monitor Log Analytics using KQL to identify the top 5 longest-running activities in ADF over the past 30 days, grouped by pipeline?",
    "answer": "First, configure Diagnostic Settings in ADF to forward pipeline/activity run telemetry to Log Analytics. The KQL query is: \n```kusto\nADFActivityRun\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(30d)\n| where Status == 'Succeeded' or Status == 'Failed'\n| extend DurationSeconds = datetime_diff('second', End, Start)\n| summarize MaxDuration = max(DurationSeconds) by PipelineName, ActivityName\n| top 5 by MaxDuration desc\n```\nThis KQL query computes the duration between Start and End timestamps, groups by pipeline and activity, and returns the top 5 activities sorted by duration.",
