    "answer": "1. Footprint: VertiPaq builds relationship mapping tables in-memory. If joining columns have high cardinality (e.g., UUIDs), the map size is huge.\n\n2. Metrics: In VertiPaq Analyzer, check the `Relationship Size` column.\n\n3. Optimization: Convert join keys to integer data types. Replace UUID strings with integer surrogate keys during ETL, reducing mapping size by up to 90%.",
