    "answer": "1. Sorting schedule: During model refresh, VertiPaq analyzes column values, builds dictionaries, and sorts them to optimize compression.\n\n2. Re-indexing: Triggered by adding new distinct values or running a full model refresh (`ProcessFull`).\n\n3. Programmatic Force: Run a TMSL script with the type set to `defragment` or execute `ProcessRecalc` on the table to force dictionary re-sorting and optimize memory space.",
