    "answer": "1. G1GC Mechanics: Divides heap into equal-sized regions (1MB to 32MB). Collects garbage in regions with the most dead space concurrently. (2) IHOP Tuning: Set `-XX:InitiatingHeapOccupancyPercent=35` (default 45). This starts GC cycles earlier, preventing heap saturation. (3) G1Reserve: Set `-XX:G1ReservePercent=15` (default 10) to allocate more backup space for allocations during shuffles, avoiding promotion failures.",
