    "answer": "During a shuffle, executors fetch partition files from other executors over the network via block transfer service. If a fetch fails due to network drops, the Shuffle Reader retries the fetch (controlled by `spark.port.maxRetries` and `spark.shuffle.io.maxRetries`). If all retries fail, Spark throws a `MetadataFetchFailedException` or `FetchFailedException`. The driver intercepts this exception, invalidates the map status of the failing executor, and resubmits the parent map stage to recreate the shuffle files, ensuring cluster fault tolerance.",
