    "answer": "AQE checks partition size metrics on shuffle map stage completion. During query planning, if the estimated size of a join input exceeds the broadcast limit, Spark plans a Sort-Merge Join. During runtime, after the map stage finishes, AQE reads the actual size of the partitions written. If the total size of one of the join inputs falls below `spark.sql.adaptive.advisoryPartitionSizeInBytes` (typically 64MB) and the broadcast threshold, AQE rebuilds the plan, broadcasts the small partition, and switches to a Broadcast Hash Join.",
