    "answer": "1. Old Estimator (7.0): Assumes all predicates are completely independent. Selectivities are multiplied (`S1 * S2 * S3`). This causes severe under-estimation for correlated attributes (e.g., Make='Ford' and Model='Mustang').\n\n2. New Estimator (2014+): Implements exponential smoothing for correlated attributes. It sorts selectivities (`S1 > S2 > S3`) and calculates: `S1 * S2^0.5 * S3^0.25`, assuming partial correlation. For joins, it uses base containment assumptions, improving estimation accuracy for composite indexes.",
