    "answer": "1. Plan Caching: When a parameterized query runs for the first time, the optimizer sniffs the input parameter values and builds an execution plan optimized for those specific values, caching it in memory.\n\n2. Sniffing issue: Subsequent executions with different parameters reuse the cached plan, which can be highly inefficient if the new parameters require scans instead of seeks.\n\n3. OPTIMIZE FOR UNKNOWN: This hint instructs the optimizer to ignore parameter values during compile time. It uses column average densities to calculate cardinality, building a balanced plan that performs acceptably across all parameters, avoiding plan regression.",
