    "question": "Describe the memory layout of the Lock Manager. How are lock hashes generated, and what is the internal performance impact of a lock hash collision?",
    "answer": "1. Lock Manager Layout: Manages active locks in a hash table structure. It allocates memory for hash buckets containing lock headers and owner blocks.\n\n2. Hash Generation: The engine generates a hash value based on the resource ID (e.g., Table ID, Page ID, or Key hash).\n\n3. Hash Collision: If multiple resources resolve to the same hash bucket, their lock blocks are chained. Under heavy concurrent workloads, collisions force threads to scan long chains to find their lock, causing lock manager CPU bottlenecks and spinlock contention on the hash buckets.",
