    "answer": "1. Deadlock Graph: Captured via the `xml_deadlock_report` Extended Event. It includes:\n- `lockmode`: The requested or held lock type (e.g., X, S, IX).\n- `status`: Whether the transaction holds the lock ('owner') or is waiting for it ('waiter').\n- `waiter-list`: The list of SPIDs waiting for that resource.\n\nAnalyzing these parameters allows developers to identify the conflicting SQL statements and index designs causing deadlocks without running trace queries.",
