    "answer": "1. Update Lock (U): Intermediate lock. Acquired during search phases of update statements.\n\n2. Conversion Deadlock: If two transactions read a row (S lock) and then attempt to update it (requesting X lock), both wait for the other to release the S lock, causing a deadlock.\n\n3. Prevention: The U lock is compatible with S locks but incompatible with other U or X locks. Only one transaction can hold a U lock on a row, preventing conversion deadlocks as only one thread is queued to convert to X.",
